er and make delays between queries. With the GeneBank-like format batch querying is also possible: <a href=\"http://rest.kegg.jp/get/hsa00053+hsa00061\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://rest.kegg.jp/get/hsa00053+hsa00061<\/a><\/p>\n\n<p>This should likely be a one-time or at least rare operation, because of the load on their server (and I don't think they make big changes very often). You can retrieve info for new pathways, once they appear in <a href=\"http://rest.kegg.jp/list/pathway/\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://rest.kegg.jp/list/pathway/<\/a>...<\/p>\n","answer_id":14565,"question_id":14561,"up_vote_count":2}],"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/14561/where-to-obtain-metabolic-pathway-datasets","last_activity_date":1390426343,"creation_date":1390411489,"answer_count":1,"title":"Where to obtain metabolic pathway datasets","body":"<p>I've been looking through the files available at <a href=\"http://www.reactome.org/\" rel=\"nofollow\">www.reactome.org<\/a> along with some others but I only find images/pdfs of metabolic pathway diagrams. Where is the actual data these pathways are drawn from? I imagine there should be some kind of directed graph representation. I'm limited to freely available datasets, so unfortunately I'm not able to check out those such as KEGG.<\/p>\n","question_id":14561,"tags":["database"],"score":2,"accepted_answer_id":14565,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":true,"view_count":97,"up_vote_count":2},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/Akzmi.png?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":4447,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/4447/crl","reputation":146,"display_name":"crl"},"answers":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/da1e8af33e12bfa60ea44b3af00c0d03?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","user_type":"moderator","user_id":5144,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/5144/chris","reputation":31001,"display_name":"Chris"},"score":1,"is_accepted":false,"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"h