 true blue rose.<\/p>\n\n<p><strong>More info<\/strong><\/p>\n\n<p>Wikipedia article <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Blue_rose\" rel=\"nofollow\">Blue Rose<\/a> gives good coverage.<\/p>\n\n<p><a href=\"http://bulbnrose.x10.mx/Heredity/King/RosePigments/RosePigments.html\" rel=\"nofollow\">Here's a nice scientific bibliography of rose pigments with some good information on blues<\/a>.<\/p>\n","answer_id":10028,"question_id":10026,"up_vote_count":3,"last_edit_date":1389846247}],"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/10026/is-there-any-natural-blue-rose","last_activity_date":1389846247,"creation_date":1377566252,"answer_count":1,"title":"Is there any natural blue rose?","body":"<p>I had recently read an article that the possibility of having natural blue rose is extremely rare because of the absence of delphinidin in most roses. Are all blue roses just a product of cross-breeding?<\/p>\n","question_id":10026,"tags":["botany","plant-anatomy","ethnobiology","pigmentation"],"score":1,"accepted_answer_id":10028,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":true,"view_count":1432,"up_vote_count":1,"last_edit_date":1377782114},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/4277666449f41474561f867f04f32b73?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":158,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/158/harpalss","reputation":1335,"display_name":"harpalss","accept_rate":74},"comments":[{"owner":{"user_type":"does_not_exist","display_name":"user5433"},"score":0,"post_id":2870,"edited":false,"creation_date":1389824382,"comment_id":19220,"body":"if there are 600 units in 1 mg surely there must be more than 1 mg for 1000 units 1000/600 = 1.67 mg?"}],"answers":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/e60c4ebf047734e923ffa4ffa45337cd?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":1122,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/1122/rwst","reputation":3115,"display_name":"rwst","accept_rate":100},"score":5,"is_acc