158/harpalss","reputation":1335,"display_name":"harpalss","accept_rate":74},"edited":false,"creation_date":1342429834,"comment_id":4214,"body":"@harpalss.  A pedantic point.  Taking the specific activity of PK to be 600U/mg, if you buy 1KU (1000 Units) then you have 1000/600 mg (~1.66 mg). If you purchase 600 Units, then you have 1 mg (provided that the specific activity measurement is correct).  Personally, I would use the lower figure for the SA, just to provide a reasonable estimate of how much protein Sigma are likely to send,  and calculate the protein content of the resuspended preparation myself (see answer below)."},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/8729233d525a654914051bf8c1234c78?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":115,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/115/nico","reputation":6011,"display_name":"nico","accept_rate":100},"score":0,"post_id":2871,"reply_to_user":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/1670879794aed7c23742e5b1f759be94?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":1136,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/1136/tomd","reputation":2087,"display_name":"TomD"},"edited":false,"creation_date":1342438031,"comment_id":4216,"body":"@TomD: I am not saying HE should do it, I am saying that is one method to do it. The Biuret method would also work, although it only gives you an approximate concentration. If weighting is not an option MS or similar should do."},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/8729233d525a654914051bf8c1234c78?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":115,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/115/nico","reputation":6011,"display_name":"nico","accept_rate":100},"score":0,"post_id":2871,"reply_to_user":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/1670879794aed7c23742e5b1f759be94?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":1136,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/1136/t