g the supplementary tables in <a href=\"http://www.plosone.org/article/info%3adoi/10.1371/journal.pone.0003128\" rel=\"nofollow\">Allsop et al<\/a> correctly, the replacement value of insect pollination to apples in the Western Cape of South Africa would represent a <strong>6%-25% increase in production cost<\/strong> (and, if the producers pass that along to the consumers, an equal increase in the cost to consumer).<\/p>\n\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"http://dx.doi.org/10.1371/journal.pone.0003128\" rel=\"nofollow\"> <strong>Allsopp MH, de Lange WJ, Veldtman R<\/strong>. 2008. Valuing insect pollination services with cost of replacement. PLoS ONE 3: e3128\u2013e3128.<\/a><\/li>\n<li><a href=\"http://dx.doi.org/10.1016/j.ecolecon.2011.08.001\" rel=\"nofollow\"> <strong>Winfree, Gross, Kremen<\/strong>. 2011. Valuing pollination services to agriculture. Ecol Econ 71: 9\u20139.<\/a> [behind paywall, but <a href=\"http://nature.berkeley.edu/kremenlab/Articles/Valuing%20Pollination%20Services%20to%20Agriculture.pdf\" rel=\"nofollow\">posted free here<\/a>]<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n","answer_id":14261,"question_id":14251,"up_vote_count":5,"last_edit_date":1389105158}],"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/14251/how-much-cost-would-artificial-pollination-add-to-common-products-fruits-etc","last_activity_date":1389105158,"creation_date":1388751158,"answer_count":1,"title":"How much cost would artificial pollination add to common products (fruits etc.)?","body":"<p>I've read about ecosystem services and their possible valuation - statements like \"honeybee pollination service in the US is worth 1.6 billion dollars\".<\/p>\n\n<p>Is data available on how this would affect the cost a consumer pays for a given product? For example if the humans must do all pollination of fruits themselves, how would that affect the retail cost of these fruit?<\/p>\n","question_id":14251,"tags":["botany","ecology","environment","ecosystem"],"score":4,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":true,"view_count